tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows good renal and electrolyte balance, and normal fasting glucose. However, HbA1c is elevated, indicating suboptimal long-term glycemic control and possible diabetes or prediabetes. Chloride is slightly above normal but not clinically significant in isolation. Recommend further evaluation and management of glycemic status.
